{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5fcb2e86-07fb-435e-941b-279b74d4a183","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 which supports constructor injection. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // sync setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async init (replaces [TestInitialize] for async work)\n    public Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test setup\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup (replaces [TestCleanup] for async work)\n    public Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test teardown\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void TestExample()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is injected automatically; no `[TestInitialize]` needed for sync setup.\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement for async per-test setup (runs after constructor).\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`** — implement for async per-test teardown.\n- You can still use `[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]` for one-time class-level setup if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"738b2389-4081-41c3-9bc4-1f1a41e1dcdb","outputTokens":360,"requestId":"581A:A737D:17DDE3F:194FFB4:6A0338AA"},"id":"2e3d4016-0bed-4e1e-bdc3-25260a2641c0","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:26:59.340Z","parentId":"14910b6a-6576-4141-abec-2afbfe5c49cd"}
